    "Results OverviewFor similarity computation, according to experimental tests, an average precision of 0.88 met the requirement for high precision and recall.",
    "The corresponding threshold value at this point was 0.855.",
    "Therefore, the threshold value for calculations of similarity was determined to be 0.855, which was used to filter out standard terms that were not similar enough to the diagnosis.After collecting the candidate data set, we used 2 LLMs and 4 techniques for prompt engineering.",
    "Subsequently, we mapped the LLM outputs to the most suitable candidate terms from the ICD-10-CN standard vocabulary, enabling us to calculate precision, recall, and F 1 -score.",
    "In order to undertake entity normalization, we selected the classic BERT series, comprising BERT, MC-BERT, and BERT-WWM, as our comparison models."
